FacebookTools:mod.ad.reject.reason.too_m: Ad image contains too much text
FacebookTools:mod.ad.reject.text.ad_forb: Facebook prohibits to advertise a range of products and services that fall under the restrictions of the laws or policies of the social network. You can read more about the list of prohibited products for advertising here: https://www.facebook.com/policies/ads/restricted_content
FacebookTools:mod.ad.reject.text.bad_qua: Adverts must not contain materials containing links to external landing pages that work in unexpected or destructive ways. This category includes: misleading advertising positioning, such as sensational headlines and attracting people to landing pages with a minimum of original content, filled mostly with extraneous or low-quality advertising materials. Learn more about Facebook rules: https://www.facebook.com/policies/ads/prohibited_content/low_quality_or_disruptive_experiences
FacebookTools:mod.ad.reject.text.before_: Adverts must not contain images “before” and “after”, as well as images of unexpected or unbelievable results. Advertising materials promoting diet and slimming products should not provoke low self-esteem in a person. Advertising for slimming and healthy lifestyle products should be targeted to people over 18 years old. Learn more about Facebook rules: https://www.facebook.com/policies/ads/prohibited_content/personal_health
FacebookTools:mod.ad.reject.text.cheatin: In adverts, you can not display images that show non-existent functions. Learn more about Facebook rules: https://www.facebook.com/policies/ads/prohibited_content/non_existent_functionality
FacebookTools:mod.ad.reject.text.errors_: Adverts must not contain offensive language or grammatical and punctuation errors. Symbols, numbers and letters should be used properly, without attempting to mislead us or other management systems during advertising checks. Learn more about Facebook rules: https://www.facebook.com/policies/ads/prohibited_content/grammar
FacebookTools:mod.ad.reject.text.forbidd: Adverts must not promote financial products and services that are often associated with fraudulent schemes: binary options, the initial placement of tokens, cryptocurrency, etc. For more information about prohibited tools, please read here: https://www.facebook.com/business/news / new-ads-security-of-financial-product-and-services-ads
FacebookTools:mod.ad.reject.text.idealiz: Adverts must not contain images “before” and “after”, as well as images of unexpected or unbelievable results. Advertising materials promoting diet and slimming products should not provoke low self-esteem in a person. Advertising for slimming and healthy lifestyle products should be targeted to people over 18 years old. Learn more about Facebook rules: https://www.facebook.com/policies/ads/prohibited_content/personal_health
FacebookTools:mod.ad.reject.text.page_no: Adverts must not redirect people to broken landing pages. This also includes materials on the landing pages that do not allow a person to leave them. Learn more about Facebook rules: https://www.facebook.com/policies/ads/prohibited_content/non_functional_landing_page
FacebookTools:mod.ad.reject.text.personi: Adverts must not contain materials that refer to personal characteristics or imply them. This includes direct or indirect reference or indication of race, ethnic origin, religion, belief, age, sexual orientation or behavior, gender identity, disability, medical condition (including physical or mental health), financial condition, union membership, criminal background or name. Learn more about Facebook’s rules: https://www.facebook.com/policies/ads/prohibited_content/personal_attributes
FacebookTools:mod.ad.reject.text.sensati: Adverts must not contain shocking, sensational materials or materials that show disrespect for people or talk about violence. Learn more about Facebook rules: https://www.facebook.com/policies/ads/prohibited_content/sensational_content
FacebookTools:mod.ad.reject.text.sexual_: Adverts must not contain materials for adults. In addition, advertising should not contain images of naked parts of the body, people in indecent postures, as well as actions that are excessively outspoken or provocative. Read more about the rules and examples of prohibited materials here: https://www.facebook.com/policies/ads/prohibited_content/adult_content
FacebookTools:mod.ad.reject.text.too_muc: Facebook recommends that the text in the image should not exceed 20% of the area. Change creative and re-enable ad. To learn more about the requirements of Facebook, go to Help - https://www.facebook.com/business/help/980593475366490). To check the amount of text in your image, use the Facebook tool: https://www.facebook.com/ads/tools/text_overlay
FacebookTools:mod.ad.reject.text.using_f: Facebook prohibits the use of the Facebook trademarks in promotional materials. Learn more here: https://www.facebook.com/policies/ads/use_of_brand_assets/brand_reference. Remove the mention of Facebook brands from promotional materials and run the ad again.

  • refill the eLama balance;

Template:direct.maxtraffic.description: The algorithm searches for the maximum amount of traffic for which the price charged does not exceed the price charged in the bid management tool. If such a volume of traffic exists, the algorithm will place a bid corresponding to this amount of traffic + step. In this case, you can set a limit on the bid in % of the price charged. If such a volume does not exist, the algorithm will place a bid equal to the price charged in the bid management tool.
